<solution>
<p><ul><li>2.48</li></ul></p><p>Because it does not matter which leg is a and which is b we call the missing leg x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{6.30}^{{2}}={6.77}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{39.69}={45.8329}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={45.8329}-{39.69}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={6.1429}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{x}^{{2}}}}=\sqrt{{{6.1429}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{2.48}</m>.</p>
</solution>
